    "description": {
      "value": "<p>With a roar, you draw on the magic of dragons to transform yourself, taking on draconic features. You gain the following benefits until the spell ends:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Blindsight.</strong> You have &amp;Reference[blindsight] with a range of 30 feet.</p></li><li><p><strong>Breath Weapon.</strong> When you cast this spell, and as a Bonus Action on subsequent turns for the duration, you can exhale shimmering energy in a 60-foot cone or 120-foot line that is 5 feet wide. Each creature in that area must make a Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 6d8]] force damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p></li><li><p><strong>Wings.</strong> Incorporeal wings sprout from your back, giving you a flying speed of 60 feet.</p></li><li><p><strong>Wing Attack.</strong> You can beat your wings as a Bonus Action. Each creature within 15 feet of you must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 2d6]] plus your spellcasting modifier bludgeoning damage and be knocked &amp;Reference[prone]. You can then fly up to half your flying speed.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Using a Higher-Level Spell Slot. </strong>If you use a slot of level 9+, this does not require your Concentration..</p>",
